Hengshui Lake National Nature Reserve welcomes thousands of migratory birds every year, of which the Baer's pochard is the rarest. Every winter, the reserve provides a refuge for birds. About 'Journeys in Nature': Hebei series Hebei Province hosts the largest forest park in northern China, Saihanba National Forest Park, and the country's largest expanse of coastal sand dunes, the Golden Coast National Nature Reserve. Here, you will find unique landforms and a rich variety of plants and animals. For more: Hebei series | Episode 1: Beautiful Highland Hebei series | Episode 2: Boundary River Hebei series | Episode 3: Wetland in the Snow Hebei series | Episode 4: The Rhythm of Winter Hebei series | Episode 5: Golden Coast Hebei series | Episode 6: Qilihai Hebei series | Episode 7: Wetland on the Plain (Cover image a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)